--- title: Exponence of «sequential» temporal semantics author: Ivan Netkachev date: 'Last update: 2024-01-10' output: html_document: number_sections: true anchor_sections: true pandoc_args: --shift-heading-level-by=-1 --- The basic temporal semantics of sequence of events ("when X occured, Y occured") is expressed either with a dedicated converb affix or a separate construction. Some constructions involve the participles combined with a locative case marker. This feature has two subfeatures, corresponding to perfective ("when X occured, Y occured") and imperfective ("when X was still occuring, Y occured") semantic contexts. ## IPFV ::: {.panel-tabset} ### Map ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
